    <text id="B0174T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Miss E. James, a teacher in Harrisonburg, writes Waldo about her belongings,
                    which had been shipped to the wrong place. She also writes that her school is
                    doing well.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Roswell Waldo</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-10-17"><abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 17<hi
                                rend="underline">
                                <hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        </hi><abbr expan=", 1868">/68</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Harrisonburg, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>One barrel marked <abbr expan="Number">No.</abbr> 2480 and two boxes 2481 and
                    2482 were 'Shipped' to me from New York on <abbr expan="Saturday">Sat.</abbr>
                    the 10<hi rend="super">th</hi> of this month in the Steamer 'Isaac Bell,' <abbr
                        expan="Government">Gov't</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Transport">Trans.</abbr> to Richmond, to go from there to Staunton,
                    by railroad.</p>

                <p>The <abbr expan="Association">Ass'n</abbr> directed them to the care of John
                    Scanton, supposing he lived in Staunton. He is known there, but lives <hi
                        rend="underline">here</hi>, has been long a resident of this town, is a
                    Union Man (Irish.) but respectable.</p>

                <p>Will you be so kind as to haul them up for me and send them on as speedily as
                    possible? <pb n="2"/>Not by express, if it is possible to send them without
                    delay in a <hi rend="underline">less</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">expensive</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">manner</hi>. Do you hear from Mr. Scott? the gentleman who
                    was to teach the colored people. My school prospers finely. I have <orig
                        reg="sixty-two">sixty two</orig> scholars and expect many more soon.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>In great haste,<lb/> Respectfully Yours</salute>
                    <signed>E James.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
